Pre-Game Insights: Mexico trained in San Diego ahead of the match and traveled to Houston on June 18.
Jaime Lozano made roster cuts and faced decisions on the starting lineup, particularly at right-back and midfield.
Julio Gonzalez is likely to start in goal, and the front three of Antuna, Gimenez, and Quinones are expected to be explosive.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Jamaica's key players include Leon Bailey, Michail Antonio, and Demarai Gray, who play in England.
Mexico's match against Jamaica is crucial for first-place aspirations in Group B.
